<P>Begin with Percentages.  For a quick reminder about the idea of percentage and the relationship between percentages and fractions, work through Level 1 Lesson 9 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 9 a~?">Section a</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 9 b 0~?">Section b</a>.  
<br>
<P>Price discounts and increases appear in day to day life.  Normally these price changes involve finding a percentage of a quantity, usually a sum of money.  Try  Level 1 Lesson 9 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 9 d 0~?">Section d</a>.  Questions    <a href="launch.htm#q0274">274</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0685">685</a> will give you a chance to test your understanding of "finding a percentage of a quantity".
<br>
<P> You should be able to "express one quantity as a percentage of another".  Examples demonstrating this skill can be found in Level 1 Lesson 9 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 9 c 0~?">Section c</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 9 e 0~?">Section e</a>.    In particular, the questions <a href="launch.htm#q0287">287</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0288">288</a> ask you to find the percentage increase and percentage decrease respectively. Try also questions <a href="launch.htm#q0285">285</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0285">286</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0684">684</a>

<br>
